# PI-Hole DNS server

##Overview
I deployed Pi-Hole as a network wide DNS ad blocker inside a Proxmox LXC container  as part of my personal home lab.

##Purpose
To filter DNS traffic at the network layer, reducing ads and tracking domains across connected devices. This approach allowed me to block ads where browser based extensions cannot be installed.

##Deployment
- Installed Pi-Hole in a Debian LXC container on Proxmox
-Initially configured using DHCP (rookie mistake) 
-Resolved my mistake by implementing a DHCP reservation on the router to ensure a consistent and predictable IP address for my DNS server.
-Configured pi-hole as the primary DNS resolver for my devices on the netwworrk

## Notes
This is the first of many services I plan to deploy on my Proxmox home-lab. I had alot of fun and learned a great bit. I encourage you to try this on your own!

